<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
For complete description, see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.889.39090" author="Hendrich, L" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="81 - 152" refId="B13" refString="Hendrich, L, Shaverdo, H, Hajek, J, Balke, M, 2019. Taxonomic revision of Australian Copelatus Erichson, 1832 (Coleoptera, Dytiscidae, Copelatinae). ZooKeys 889: 81 - 152, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.889.39090" title="Taxonomic revision of Australian Copelatus Erichson, 1832 (Coleoptera, Dytiscidae, Copelatinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.889.39090" volume="889" year="2019">Hendrich et al. (2019)</bibRefCitation>
. Medium sized (TL: 5.0-
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.7" unit="mm" value="5.7">5.7 mm</quantity>
), oblong-oval species. Species variable in elytral colouration: elytra from almost uniformly dark brown to black with only base and lateral sides yellowish, to almost yellowish-orange coloured with dark stripes along elytral striae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 5, 6" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 5, 6. Habitus of Copelatus 5 C. portior Guignot, 1956 (male, Guadalcanal; TL: 5.2 mm) 6 C. portior (striolate female, Papua; TL: 4.7 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1023.61478.figures5-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/519050" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">5</figureCitation>
). Elytron with well-impressed six discal striae and a submarginal stria. Female dimorphic; striolate form with dorsal surface almost black, matt and with coarse microreticulation and numerous strioles on elytra and pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 5, 6" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 5, 6. Habitus of Copelatus 5 C. portior Guignot, 1956 (male, Guadalcanal; TL: 5.2 mm) 6 C. portior (striolate female, Papua; TL: 4.7 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1023.61478.figures5-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/519050" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">6</figureCitation>
). Median lobe in lateral view sickle-shaped; broad and subparallel in basal two thirds, thin and regularly curved in apical third; a distinct hammer-like process present in two thirds on ventral side (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 19. Male genitalia of Copelatus portior Guignot, 1956 (Australia) A median lobe in lateral view, right side B median lobe in lateral view, left side C median lobe in ventral view D left paramere in external view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1023.61478.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/519058" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">19</figureCitation>
). Parameres broad, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“D”">&quot;D&quot;</normalizedToken>
-shaped; apical lobes moderately long, club-shaped.
</paragraph>
